    <note>Cai(1) Shu(2) [12046] According to Liu(2) Zai's funerary inscription for his daughter, Wang(2) Wanshu's [12051] wife, he and his father refused to take office during the Chongning and Daguan periods and the world (tianxia) respected them (gao zhi) for it. Shu(2) moved to an area on the Changzhou-Suzhou border. I am guessing Wujin since that was where Shen(2)'s [12023] branch of the lineage moved. See Liu Zai, WJ, 34.13b.</note>
